column96: IGF::CT::IGF  THE DISA WLAN NETWORK IS BASED ON THE WIRELESS LAN SOLUTION COMPONENTS FROM ARUBA NETWORKS. THE WLAN PROVIDES AN ENTERPRISE CAPABILITY TO ALLOW WIRELESS ACCESS FROM ANY DISA CAC- ENABLED LAPTOP TO THE DISANET NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE FROM AREAS LOCATED WITHIN THE DISA FT. MEADE CAMPUS.
column97: IGF::OT::IGF  DISA HAS A REQUIREMENT FOR THE DEPLOYMENT OF A WIRELESS MOBILITY SOLUTION THAT WILL INTEGRATE INTO THE EXISTING WLAN ARCHITECTURE AS WELL AS INTEGRATE WITH THE EXISTING MDM AND BLACKBERRY MANAGEMENT PLATFORMS.  SUSTAINMENT FOR THE CURRENT WLAN SOLUTION AND SERVICES AT FT MEADE IS FOCUSED ON WLAN MONITORING, MAINTENANCE AND TROUBLESHOOTING, SYSTEM ADMINISTRATION AND INFORMATION ASSURANCE MAINTENANCE AND TROUBLESHOOTING BY CONTRACTOR PERSONNEL.
